		"description":{
			"value":"<p class=\"flavour\"><em>Embedded in you back, this hidden hand crossbow springs to life at your whim.</em></p><p class=\"basics\"><strong>Weapon:</strong> Hand crossbow (embedded component)</p><p class=\"basics\"><strong>Enhancement Bonus:</strong> Attack Rolls and Damage Rolls</p><p class=\"basics\"><strong>Critical:</strong> +2d6 critical damage</p><p><strong>Requirement:</strong> You must be a warforged and have the living construct racial trait to use this item.</p><p class=\"subheading\"><strong>Property:</strong></p><p>This magic crossbow is attached to or embedded in your back. With a minor action, you can mentally command it to rise to a position on your shoulder. Once it's in position, you can fire a shoulderbow as a standard action by using a mental command and no hands at all. The shoulderbow generates its own ammunition. These bolts disappear 1 round after they are fired or removed from the bow.</p><p class=\"subheading\"><strong>Power âœ¦ Daily (Minor Action)</strong></p><p>Make a ranged basic attack with the shoulderbow.</p>",
